# Business Requirements

## Project

Project Horus

## Organization

Horus Technologies

## Phase

Phase 1 – Active Directory Security Modernization

---

# Purpose

This document defines the business requirements supporting the implementation of a modern Active Directory infrastructure.

---

# Business Requirements

## BR-001 – Centralized Identity Management

The organization shall maintain a centralized directory service to manage users, computers, and security groups from a single administrative platform.

---

## BR-002 – Secure Authentication Services

The infrastructure shall provide secure authentication and authorization services for all domain-joined systems.

---

## BR-003 – Role-Based Access Control

Administrative permissions shall be assigned according to job function and least-privilege principles.

---

## BR-004 – Administrative Separation

Privileged administrative activities shall be separated from standard user activities through dedicated administrative accounts.

---

## BR-005 – Standardized Resource Organization

Directory objects shall be organized using a structured Organizational Unit (OU) hierarchy to support delegated administration and Group Policy application.

---

## BR-006 – Name Standardization

Servers, workstations, user accounts, security groups, and organizational units shall follow documented naming conventions.

---

## BR-007 – Scalability

The Active Directory design shall support future expansion without requiring significant architectural changes.

---

## BR-008 – Operational Documentation

All deployment, configuration, and validation activities shall be documented to support operational continuity and knowledge transfer.

---

## BR-009 – Security Baseline Foundation

The Active Directory environment shall provide a foundation for future security controls, including Group Policy enforcement, endpoint hardening, vulnerability management, and monitoring capabilities.

---

# Approval

These requirements serve as the baseline business objectives for Phase 1 of Project Horus.
